
/*
 * 1. `@.arguments` - This iterator retrieves the first node named "arguments" from the current context. It is typically used to access the arguments passed into a function or slot in Hyperlambda.
 * 2. `*` - This iterator retrieves all children nodes of the "arguments" node. It is used to access each argument passed to the function or slot.
 * 3. `/message` - This iterator filters the result set to include only those nodes named "message" among the children of the "arguments" node. It is used to specifically access the "message" argument if it exists.
 */

.:x:@.arguments/*/message